April 18, 2008.People.com, April 18th - A summary of Taiwanese news - Tsai Ying-wen confirmed she will also join the competition for Democratic Progressive Party chairman.Today at 3 o'clock in the afternoon, Tsai Ying-wen went to the Democratic Progressive Party headquarters to register as a candidate. She put forth three expectations for the Democratic Progressive Party: modesty, efficiency, tolerance.After Tsai Ying-wen finished the registration procedure, she said to the media that the Democratic Progressive Party should first return to modesty - be an opposition party with ruling experience. Secondly, the Democratic Progressive Party should turn theories into policies - it should have efficiency.Also, the Democratic Progressive Party should be more tolerant. It should be tolerant regardless of ethnicity and ideology.